{
  "texts": [
    "For any principal possibility frame F:1.",
    "F satisfies R-rule and R⇒win; 2.",
    "F is R-tight iff F is strong.Proof.",
    "Let F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ be a principal possibility frame.For part 1, suppose F does not satisfy R-rule, so we have x ′ ⊑ x and x ′ R i y ′ ≬ z, but for all y, if xR i y, then y ⊥ z, so y ⊑ z *.",
    "Hence x ∈ ■ i ↓z *, but x ′ ̸ ∈ ■ i ↓z *, so ■ i ↓z * does not satisfy persistence."
  ]
}